<div class="audio-streaming-container" data-controller="audio-recorder">
  <div class="header">
    <h1>Audio Streaming to Bunny.net</h1>
    <p>Record audio directly to Bunny.net streaming service. No local storage required.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="recording-controls">
    <button
      data-audio-recorder-target="button"
      data-action="click->audio-recorder#toggleRecording"
      class="record-button btn btn-primary"
      type="button">
      Start Recording
    </button>
  </div>

  <div class="status-display">
    <p data-audio-recorder-target="status" class="status-text">
      Ready to record
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="info">
    <h3>Configuration</h3>
    <p>Make sure to set your Bunny.net credentials in environment variables:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>BUNNY_STREAM_LIBRARY_ID</code> - Your stream library ID</li>
      <li><code>BUNNY_STREAM_KEY</code> - Your stream access key</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Or pass them as parameters: <code>?stream_library_id=XXX&stream_key=YYY</code></p>
  </div>
</div>